cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.NI, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with covert communication over interference channels, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and security and privacy (cs.CR). The use of a warden to detect covert communication also falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The extension of the results to multiple wardens involves system and control (cs.SI).
